The paper deals with person re-identification, which is a computer vision problem, and proposes a novel model for part alignment using convolutional neural networks. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves multi-task learning and attention mechanisms, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed model is evaluated on large-scale datasets, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with pedestrian detection and alignment, which is a sub-topic of computer vision and robotics (cs.CR).
